cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the optimization of overlay networks for large organizations with users in multiple sites connected over the Internet. It also involves the use of a Predictive Flow Optimizer (PFO) and an online tier, MONtra, to solve non-concave utility maximization problems. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) as it involves the optimization of communication between multiple sites for the most benefit to the organization. 

The sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) is also likely as the paper deals with the orchestration of communication between multiple sites for the optimal benefit of the organization. 

The sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) is a possibility as the paper deals with the optimization of communication between multiple sites, which could involve security considerations. 

Finally, the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) is a possibility as the paper deals with the optimization of communication between multiple sites, which could involve distributed computing considerations.
